Dataset: Hotel booking demand

Sourse: https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/jessemostipak/hotel-booking-demand
This data set contains:
- ~100 000 booking records
- 32 columns
- booking information 
The data is originally from the article Hotel Booking Demand Datasets, written by Nuno Antonio, Ana Almeida, and Luis Nunes for Data in Brief, Volume 22, February 2019.

This dataset was chosen because:
- it is realistic (used in hotel industry research),
- it contains rich booking behavior,
- it is useful for AI-driven business analytics.


  Field    -----    Meaning 
 • hotel — The type of hotel (City Hotel / Resort Hotel).
 • is_canceled — Whether the booking was canceled (1 = yes, 0 = no).
 • lead_time — Number of days between the booking date and the arrival date.
 • arrival_date_year — Year of the guest’s arrival.
 • arrival_date_month — Month of arrival.
 • arrival_date_week_number — Week number of the year (1–52).
 • arrival_date_day_of_month — Day of the month (1–31).
 • stays_in_weekend_nights — Number of weekend nights in the stay.
 • stays_in_week_nights — Number of weekday nights in the stay.
 • children — Number of children.
 • babies — Number of infants.
 • meal — Type of meal plan (BB = breakfast, HB = half-board, SC = no meals, etc.).
 • country — Guest’s country of residence.
 • market_segment — Market segment (e.g., Online Travel Agency, Corporate, Direct).
 • distribution_channel — Booking channel (e.g., TA, Direct, GDS).
 • is_repeated_guest — Whether the guest has stayed before (1 = yes, 0 = no).
 • previous_cancellations — Number of previous bookings this guest canceled.
 • previous_bookings_not_canceled — Number of past successful stays (not canceled).
 • reserved_room_type — The room type that the guest booked originally.
 • assigned_room_type — The room type actually assigned at check-in.
 • booking_changes — How many times the booking was modified.
 • deposit_type — Whether the guest paid a deposit and what type (No, Non-Refund, Refundable).
 • agent — ID of the booking agent.
 • company — ID of the company making the booking (if any).
 • days_in_waiting_list — How many days the booking remained on the waiting list.
 • customer_type — Type of customer (Transient, Group, Contract, etc.).
 • adr — ADR (Average Daily Rate) — price per night for the stay.
 • required_car_parking_spaces — Number of parking spaces the guest requested.
 • total_of_special_requests — Total number of special requests (e.g., extra pillows, higher floor).
 • reservation_status — Final status: Checked-Out, Canceled, No-Show.
 • reservation_status_date — The date when the reservation status was updated.
